I'll be there in an hour.

746
00:50:30,679 --> 00:50:31,811
[Ann] Jenny, are you
skating today?

747
00:50:31,941 --> 00:50:33,378
-[Jennifer] Yeah.
-[Ann] Get your skates.

748
00:50:33,508 --> 00:50:34,596
[Jennifer] I'm brushing
my hair!

749
00:50:34,727 --> 00:50:36,990
Okay, I got your skates.
Come on, quick!

750
00:50:37,121 --> 00:50:39,775
Look it, he's not going
to be killing kids
getting off a school bus.

751
00:50:39,906 --> 00:50:41,821
You and everybody else
are doing exactly
what he wants.

752
00:50:41,951 --> 00:50:43,344
Oh, yeah?

753
00:50:43,475 --> 00:50:44,911
That's right.

754
00:50:45,042 --> 00:50:46,913
He's rattling
everybody's cage.

755
00:50:47,044 --> 00:50:49,176
He's getting off
on the attention.

756
00:50:49,307 --> 00:50:53,615
And you are willing to risk
your own kids' lives
that you're right.

757
00:50:53,746 --> 00:50:56,705
Jon, this psycho
has been getting away
with killing people

758
00:50:56,836 --> 00:50:58,794
and writing you
about it for years.

759
00:50:58,925 --> 00:51:01,275
Maybe he's talking
about Jennifer and Suzy
specifically.

760
00:51:01,406 --> 00:51:02,842
I can't take that chance.

761
00:51:02,972 --> 00:51:05,497
"I shall no longer announce
when I commit my murders.

762
00:51:05,627 --> 00:51:09,022
They shall look like
routine incidents."

763
00:51:09,153 --> 00:51:11,068
Maybe then you can forget
this whole damn thing.

764
00:51:11,198 --> 00:51:14,375
"Only you, Jon, will know
when I do my thing."

765
00:51:14,506 --> 00:51:16,595
He's dumping
the whole thing
back on me.

766
00:51:16,725 --> 00:51:18,249
You know, you are
scaring me, Jon.

767
00:51:18,379 --> 00:51:19,163
You're scaring me to death.

768
00:51:19,641 --> 00:51:20,729
Hey.

769
00:51:21,730 --> 00:51:23,341
Take it easy, okay?

770
00:51:26,735 --> 00:51:29,477
You don't even see
what you're doing
to this family, do you?

771
00:51:29,608 --> 00:51:31,088
Girls, come on!
Right away!

772
00:51:47,843 --> 00:51:49,584
Are you going
to be late again?

773
00:51:49,715 --> 00:51:51,369
No. I'm going to try
to get home early.

774
00:51:51,499 --> 00:51:52,761
-Great.
-Good.

775
00:51:52,892 --> 00:51:53,893
You guys have
a good day, all right?

776
00:51:54,023 --> 00:51:55,242
-Okay. Bye.
-Bye, Dad.

777
00:51:55,373 --> 00:51:56,243
Bye!

778
00:52:00,204 --> 00:52:03,685
-Hey, Jon.
-Hey, Harry.
How are you?

779
00:52:03,816 --> 00:52:05,339
When are you going
to do something
about this nut?

780
00:52:05,470 --> 00:52:07,428
He's making us all
a little jumpy.

781
00:52:07,559 --> 00:52:09,517
Harry, is
that gun loaded?

782
00:52:09,648 --> 00:52:10,823
Of course
it's loaded.

783
00:52:10,953 --> 00:52:11,867
What good's
an unloaded gun?

784
00:52:11,998 --> 00:52:13,913
Give it to me.

785
00:52:14,043 --> 00:52:15,436
Everybody's
packing something.

786
00:52:17,090 --> 00:52:20,006
I know.
Just give it to me.

787
00:52:20,137 --> 00:52:23,531
Shit, man, you know
I'm basically
a nonviolent person,

788
00:52:23,662 --> 00:52:26,055
but when people start
shooting at my kids,
I'm shooting back.

789
00:52:26,186 --> 00:52:27,883
I don't blame you.
Now give it to me.

790
00:52:28,014 --> 00:52:29,842
I'll return it to your house.
I'll come by and visit.

791
00:52:38,807 --> 00:52:40,461
I'll be by, all right?

792
00:52:41,941 --> 00:52:42,942
Shit.

793
00:52:55,041 --> 00:52:56,303
Hi, Kathy.
How you doing?

794
00:52:57,522 --> 00:52:58,566
You want
the usual?

795
00:53:01,874 --> 00:53:03,223
Yes, please.

796
00:53:24,244 --> 00:53:26,377
Can I have a cup
of coffee, please?

797
00:53:26,507 --> 00:53:29,554
To go.
Cream and sugar.

798
00:53:32,861 --> 00:53:34,428
Stop hounding me.

799
00:53:35,603 --> 00:53:37,344
Thank you.

800
00:53:37,475 --> 00:53:39,868
I don't have to answer
your questions anymore,
and you know it.

801
00:53:39,999 --> 00:53:41,435
And I'm sick and tired
of losing jobs

802
00:53:41,566 --> 00:53:43,524
and having people
afraid of me

803
00:53:43,655 --> 00:53:46,571
because of the questions
you ask them about me.

804
00:53:46,701 --> 00:53:47,702
I'm sorry
about that, Lloyd.

805
00:53:50,618 --> 00:53:51,837
I just want you
to remember one thing.

806
00:53:53,839 --> 00:53:55,406
No matter where you go,

807
00:53:55,536 --> 00:53:57,277
no matter what you do,

808
00:53:58,844 --> 00:54:00,628
I'm going to be there.

809
00:54:01,194 --> 00:54:02,587
Watching you.

810
00:54:06,112 --> 00:54:08,636
Everybody's
afraid up here,

811
00:54:08,767 --> 00:54:10,682
because of
the murders and all.

812
00:54:10,812 --> 00:54:13,337
Every time I turn
around, there's you!

813
00:54:13,467 --> 00:54:14,468
It isn't fair.

814
00:54:14,599 --> 00:54:15,730
Why are you
doing this to me?

815
00:54:15,861 --> 00:54:17,515
Why are you trying
to ruin my life?

816
00:54:17,645 --> 00:54:20,039
Will you stop
hounding me,
God damn it?

817
00:54:20,169 --> 00:54:22,084
Stop hounding me!

818
00:54:22,215 --> 00:54:24,652
Do your job!
Catch this
son of a bitch!

819
00:54:28,177 --> 00:54:29,440
I will.

820
00:54:31,964 --> 00:54:33,313
[chatter over police radio]

821
00:55:12,396 --> 00:55:15,529
Well, he says you've
already cost him two jobs.
His friends and family

822
00:55:15,660 --> 00:55:17,052
won't talk to him.

823
00:55:17,183 --> 00:55:19,664
He has no friends,
and his family's
scared to death of him.

824
00:55:21,709 --> 00:55:23,189
He says he can't
go back to school.

825
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:27,019
He's claiming for physical
and psychological damages.

826
00:55:27,149 --> 00:55:28,934
According to this,
he's even getting
death threats

827
00:55:29,064 --> 00:55:29,935
-from some of
the victims' families.
-[coughing]

828
00:55:30,065 --> 00:55:32,851
Good.

829
00:55:32,981 --> 00:55:34,679
Jon, come on. Put yourself
in his shoes for a second.

830
00:55:34,809 --> 00:55:35,984
I have!

831
00:55:36,115 --> 00:55:37,638
He's the guy!

832
00:55:42,817 --> 00:55:43,644
And you know it!

833
00:55:47,822 --> 00:55:50,956
[Fredricks] Jon, look, I know
the pressure you're under,

834
00:55:51,086 --> 00:55:52,958
and I know your hunch
is usually right,

835
00:55:53,088 --> 00:55:54,699
but I'm telling you,

836
00:55:54,829 --> 00:55:56,744
you know we can't go
into court on a hunch.

837
00:55:56,875 --> 00:55:59,443
It's not
admissible evidence.

838
00:55:59,573 --> 00:56:02,054
[Payne] Christ, Jon,
look at yourself.
You look like a mess.

839
00:56:02,184 --> 00:56:04,883
You want it to be him
so bad you're giving
yourself ulcers.

840
00:56:05,013 --> 00:56:07,059
You got to get
Lloyd Carl Warden
out of your head.

841
00:56:07,189 --> 00:56:08,974
He's been through every
frigging agency in the show.

842
00:56:09,104 --> 00:56:10,628
Fuck you.

843
00:56:10,758 --> 00:56:14,458
He's a freak, there's
no doubt about that,
but he's clean.

844
00:56:14,588 --> 00:56:17,112
Look, you've been
killing yourself on this
one for eight years.

845
00:56:17,243 --> 00:56:19,027
-We all appreciate it.
-Don't do it to me.
Don't do it to me.

846
00:56:19,158 --> 00:56:20,812
-I got to take you off
for your own good.
-Don't do it to me.

847
00:56:20,942 --> 00:56:22,857
Don't do it to me!

848
00:56:22,988 --> 00:56:25,207
Brownlee's going to
work with Fredricks
on this mess.

849
00:56:25,338 --> 00:56:27,035
You're going to
go on to other cases.

850
00:56:32,650 --> 00:56:34,129
[siren wailing]

851
00:56:34,260 --> 00:56:35,696
[dispatcher over radio] <i>
Possible hostage situation.</i>

852
00:56:35,827 --> 00:56:38,307
<i>Perp is one male, white,</i><i>
six feet tall,</i>

853
00:56:38,438 --> 00:56:40,397
<i>weighs approximately</i><i>
250 pounds.</i>

854
00:56:44,313 --> 00:56:45,924
[Brownlee] Okay,
just calm down.

855
00:56:46,054 --> 00:56:48,666
[man] He just pulled out
a gun and started
waving it around!

856
00:56:48,796 --> 00:56:50,232
He said he was
the Scorekeeper.

857
00:56:50,363 --> 00:56:51,712
I think we finally got
the son of a bitch, Jon.

858
00:56:51,843 --> 00:56:52,931
Lloyd Carl Warden?

859
00:56:53,061 --> 00:56:54,933
-Don't know.
-[chattering]

860
00:56:55,063 --> 00:56:58,023
It's an old-style
peepshow room.
We got it surrounded.

861
00:56:58,153 --> 00:56:59,459
He's got no way
out of there.

862
00:56:59,590 --> 00:57:01,113
-Is he in here?
-Yeah, in the middle
of that one.

863
00:57:01,243 --> 00:57:03,202
Careful,
he might go off.

864
00:57:03,332 --> 00:57:04,856
What the hell are
you doing here?

865
00:57:04,986 --> 00:57:06,988
Just here to share
in the glory you
don't deserve?

866
00:57:07,119 --> 00:57:09,730
-[man] Anybody comes
in here, she's dead!
-[woman] No!

867
00:57:09,861 --> 00:57:10,905
-Jon!
-My God!

868
00:57:11,036 --> 00:57:12,472
[woman crying]

869
00:57:16,215 --> 00:57:17,695
Who the fuck
are you?

870
00:57:17,825 --> 00:57:19,348
-[Brownlee] Damn!
-[woman] Please help me!

871
00:57:19,479 --> 00:57:21,307
-[Lucca] Who the fuck are you?
-You know
who the fuck I am.

872
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:23,352
[Lucca] No, I don't know
who you are.
Who are you?

873
00:57:23,483 --> 00:57:25,833
I'm the fuckin'
Scorekeeper, man!

874
00:57:25,964 --> 00:57:27,313
-The hell you are, buddy!
-If you don't get me
out of here safe

875
00:57:27,444 --> 00:57:28,967
and put that gun
down now,

876
00:57:29,097 --> 00:57:31,099
I'm going to blow
this bitch away.

877
00:57:31,796 --> 00:57:32,884
Move it!

878
00:57:34,015 --> 00:57:36,844
All right.
Here you go.

879
00:57:36,975 --> 00:57:38,280
Get the gun away
from her head.

880
00:57:38,411 --> 00:57:39,586
-No way!
-Help me.

881
00:57:39,717 --> 00:57:41,109
All right,
get the gun away
from her head.

882
00:57:41,240 --> 00:57:42,763
Put it down now!

883
00:57:44,025 --> 00:57:46,506
All right.

884
00:57:46,637 --> 00:57:49,727
You're some lonely
piece of shit
looking for attention.

885
00:57:49,857 --> 00:57:52,033
-Who the fuck is this guy?
-Come on...

886
00:57:52,164 --> 00:57:53,208
Get him
out of here now,

887
00:57:53,339 --> 00:57:55,602
or I'll blow her
away, I mean it!

888
00:57:57,778 --> 00:57:59,214
You know what?

889
00:57:59,345 --> 00:58:00,955
I don't think you
ever killed anybody.

890
00:58:01,086 --> 00:58:02,348
I don't think you
ever killed anybody
in your life.

891
00:58:02,479 --> 00:58:04,132
You wouldn't
know a thing!

892
00:58:04,263 --> 00:58:06,221
-You've never killed
anybody in your life.
-I'll kill this bitch now!

893
00:58:06,352 --> 00:58:07,962
You ain't gonna start now.
You ain't got
the balls for it.

894
00:58:08,093 --> 00:58:09,181
-Get that gun away!
-I'm going to do it!

895
00:58:09,311 --> 00:58:10,791
Get that fucking gun...

896
00:58:12,097 --> 00:58:13,141
[woman screaming]

897
00:58:14,795 --> 00:58:16,057
[all clamoring]

898
00:58:19,191 --> 00:58:22,673
Upon searching the deceased
suspect's apartment, we found
a cache of weapons,

899
00:58:22,803 --> 00:58:24,370
including a .357 Magnum

900
00:58:24,501 --> 00:58:25,980
which we believe
might've been

901
00:58:26,111 --> 00:58:28,330
the weapon used
in the Scorekeeper murders.

902
00:58:28,461 --> 00:58:30,942
Ballistic tests
are currently underway.

903
00:58:31,072 --> 00:58:33,422
Also recovered were maps
and newspaper clippings

904
00:58:33,553 --> 00:58:35,773
related to
the Scorekeeper murders.

905
00:58:35,903 --> 00:58:37,949
As of this time,
we are confident

906
00:58:38,079 --> 00:58:39,690
that we've put an end
to his reign of terror.

907
00:58:41,256 --> 00:58:43,345
Lieutenant Lucca
is in good condition.

908
00:58:43,476 --> 00:58:45,826
We are all
very thankful to him
for his bravery.

909
00:58:46,784 --> 00:58:48,089
[all clamoring]

910
00:58:58,056 --> 00:58:59,361
"Having
a not-so-wonderful time.

911
00:58:59,492 --> 00:59:02,234
Wish you were here,
Ron and George and Michael."

912
00:59:16,857 --> 00:59:17,815
Look.

913
00:59:18,467 --> 00:59:20,339
Okay.

914
00:59:20,469 --> 00:59:22,776
Things are
coming along nicely.

915
00:59:22,907 --> 00:59:23,995
The muscle tissue
that the bullet hit

916
00:59:24,125 --> 00:59:25,866
is healing nicely,
as is the wound.

917
00:59:25,997 --> 00:59:27,825
You should be
out of here in no time.

918
00:59:27,955 --> 00:59:30,131
However, we have
found something

919
00:59:30,262 --> 00:59:33,047
that concerns me
greatly.

920
00:59:33,178 --> 00:59:36,311
You are developing some
nasty-looking ulcers,
Detective Lucca.

921
00:59:36,442 --> 00:59:38,879
What it boils down to is that
you are going to have to

922
00:59:39,010 --> 00:59:41,229
drastically change
your lifestyle.

923
00:59:41,360 --> 00:59:43,275
You got to quit drinking,
quit smoking.

924
00:59:43,405 --> 00:59:44,668
You should probably
quit your job.

925
00:59:44,798 --> 00:59:47,105
At the very least,
you should take
a vacation.

926
00:59:50,412 --> 00:59:53,154
Girls, be careful
you don't slip.
The deck is wet.

927
00:59:53,285 --> 00:59:54,939
Careful. Come on,
guys, help.

928
00:59:55,069 --> 00:59:57,245
-I caught you back.
-Did not!

929
00:59:58,203 --> 00:59:59,465
Please...

930
00:59:59,596 --> 01:00:01,162
You guys just
help us, please?

931
01:00:01,293 --> 01:00:02,642
Oh, gross!

932
01:00:04,644 --> 01:00:06,472
-I bet he's got a hard-on.
-Hey.

933
01:00:06,603 --> 01:00:07,778
-You're it.
-No, you're it.

934
01:00:07,908 --> 01:00:08,909
Help me,
come on, come on.

935
01:00:19,006 --> 01:00:20,007
Hey!

936
01:00:20,834 --> 01:00:21,922
Hey!

937
01:00:22,967 --> 01:00:23,837
Hey!

938
01:00:28,189 --> 01:00:29,277
Jon.

939
01:00:30,322 --> 01:00:31,540
Jon?

940
01:00:31,671 --> 01:00:33,673
You're scaring
the girls. Please.

941
01:00:43,030 --> 01:00:46,947
You know,
it was another woman.

942
01:00:49,080 --> 01:00:51,430
You know,

943
01:00:51,560 --> 01:00:55,260
something I could
read about in <i>Cosmo...</i>

944
01:00:59,046 --> 01:01:01,658
Lament to
my girlfriends about.

945
01:01:05,879 --> 01:01:07,881
If I could,

946
01:01:08,012 --> 01:01:09,448
if I didn't
have the girls...

947
01:01:12,625 --> 01:01:14,671
I'd blow his brains out.

948
01:01:16,020 --> 01:01:17,195
I swear to God
I would.

949
01:01:20,328 --> 01:01:22,896
Just to put an end
to all of this,
just to...

950
01:01:25,464 --> 01:01:26,987
Get you back.

951
01:01:29,555 --> 01:01:30,991
[thunder rumbling]

952
01:01:35,517 --> 01:01:37,694
[Brownlee] They want to
give all of us citations.

953
01:01:41,349 --> 01:01:42,481
What for?

954
01:01:44,613 --> 01:01:46,703
We know
the guy you shot
wasn't him.

955
01:01:48,443 --> 01:01:52,056
As far
as I'm concerned,
it was him.

956
01:01:52,186 --> 01:01:53,971
[refilling glass]

957
01:01:54,101 --> 01:01:55,146
It's over,
and I'm glad it is.

958
01:02:03,415 --> 01:02:04,503
I've decided
to leave Homicide.

959
01:02:07,506 --> 01:02:08,725
I've seen
what this case
has done to you,

960
01:02:08,855 --> 01:02:12,380
and I'm not going to
let it happen to me.

961
01:02:12,511 --> 01:02:15,644
If I was you,
I'd start thinking
about doing the same thing.

962
01:02:17,385 --> 01:02:20,040
You and I have seen
enough dead bodies
to last a lifetime.

963
01:02:21,346 --> 01:02:22,477
What are you
going to do?

964
01:02:25,219 --> 01:02:26,786
Vice might be fun.

965
01:02:28,266 --> 01:02:30,137
Then again,

966
01:02:30,268 --> 01:02:31,922
pawnshop detail
would be okay, too.

967
01:02:32,531 --> 01:02:34,011
[both chuckling]

968
01:02:34,141 --> 01:02:35,099
[clinking]

969
01:02:38,667 --> 01:02:39,973
[Ann grunting]

970
01:02:40,495 --> 01:02:42,149
Jon? Uh...

971
01:02:49,156 --> 01:02:50,114
Ow!

972
01:02:56,207 --> 01:02:57,382
Almost...

973
01:02:57,512 --> 01:02:58,557
Honey?

974
01:02:58,687 --> 01:02:59,993
[coughs]

975
01:03:04,650 --> 01:03:06,260
I'll be all right.

976
01:03:07,435 --> 01:03:09,046
Just give me a second.

977
01:03:55,440 --> 01:03:56,615
[Lucca] <i>When I was a cop,</i>

978
01:03:56,745 --> 01:03:58,182
<i>I was confronted</i><i>
all the time</i>

979
01:03:58,312 --> 01:03:59,618
<i>by people</i><i>
who absolutely knew</i>

980
01:03:59,748 --> 01:04:01,446
<i>the killer</i><i>
of someone they loved.</i>

981
01:04:02,795 --> 01:04:04,753
But they
couldn't prove it.

982
01:04:04,884 --> 01:04:06,494
The killer
was going to get away.

983
01:04:07,669 --> 01:04:10,324
They wanted to run over
the bastard

984
01:04:10,455 --> 01:04:12,370
and walk out of the dark
and blow him away.

985
01:04:14,154 --> 01:04:15,895
But I always
talked them out of it.

986
01:04:17,854 --> 01:04:19,290
<i>And that night,</i><i>
there I was,</i>

