01:20:08,847 --> 01:20:10,457
which is what you
want me to do, huh?

1237
01:20:10,588 --> 01:20:12,242
Well, I can't help you!

1238
01:20:12,372 --> 01:20:14,461
It's over!

1239
01:20:14,592 --> 01:20:17,943
We both know
you're the real
last victim.

1240
01:20:18,074 --> 01:20:19,292
[coughing]

1241
01:20:19,423 --> 01:20:21,468
The last victim
of your own obsession.

1242
01:20:21,599 --> 01:20:23,122
So fucking jump!

1243
01:20:26,691 --> 01:20:28,388
Better yet...

1244
01:20:28,519 --> 01:20:30,477
[car horn honks]

1245
01:20:30,608 --> 01:20:33,393
...crawl back to your
shitty little room
and die,

1246
01:20:33,524 --> 01:20:36,353
not knowing the truth,
leaving me alone,

1247
01:20:36,483 --> 01:20:39,617
leaving the world
at risk, your world,
unguarded,

1248
01:20:39,747 --> 01:20:41,184
because
he's still out there!

1249
01:20:44,230 --> 01:20:48,104
And worst of all,
you won't be here

1250
01:20:48,234 --> 01:20:50,323
to know what happens
to friend or foe.

1251
01:20:53,761 --> 01:20:54,850
Die!

1252
01:20:56,721 --> 01:20:57,983
Die!

1253
01:21:02,596 --> 01:21:03,510
[coughing]

1254
01:21:09,386 --> 01:21:10,561
Feel better?

1255
01:21:17,655 --> 01:21:18,874
Jon...

1256
01:21:20,310 --> 01:21:22,225
What the fuck
did I ever do to you?

1257
01:21:25,271 --> 01:21:26,359
I'm sorry.

1258
01:21:28,231 --> 01:21:29,188
What?

1259
01:21:30,668 --> 01:21:32,278
You're sorry?

1260
01:21:32,409 --> 01:21:34,628
You're fucking sorry,
you piece of shit?

1261
01:21:34,759 --> 01:21:37,196
You're fucking sor...
[laughing] Sorry!

1262
01:21:51,210 --> 01:21:53,169
Jon...

1263
01:21:53,299 --> 01:21:55,432
I believe I can help you
after all.

1264
01:22:04,397 --> 01:22:05,964
[humming theme to <i>Big Valley]</i>

1265
01:22:28,465 --> 01:22:30,249
[imitates gun firing]

1266
01:22:30,380 --> 01:22:32,295
[continues humming
theme to <i>Big Valley]</i>

1267
01:22:35,167 --> 01:22:36,299
[chuckles]

1268
01:22:37,517 --> 01:22:39,302
Amazing.

1269
01:22:39,432 --> 01:22:40,781
After all you've done,

1270
01:22:40,912 --> 01:22:43,045
I can still look upon you
with mercy.

1271
01:22:43,175 --> 01:22:44,307
[muffled yelling]

1272
01:22:44,437 --> 01:22:45,612
I will give you
what you want.

1273
01:22:48,615 --> 01:22:50,487
You know why I am
the way I am?

1274
01:22:50,617 --> 01:22:53,272
Because I'm free!
[laughs]

1275
01:22:54,578 --> 01:22:56,188
Man created civilization

1276
01:22:56,319 --> 01:22:58,060
to protect himself
from himself.

1277
01:22:58,190 --> 01:22:59,365
[pounding]

1278
01:22:59,496 --> 01:23:01,759
But civilization
has one major drawback.

1279
01:23:01,889 --> 01:23:03,891
Frustration.

1280
01:23:04,022 --> 01:23:06,720
So to deal with
this frustration,

1281
01:23:06,851 --> 01:23:08,418
society has set up
a system

1282
01:23:08,548 --> 01:23:11,682
of laws and
moral prohibitions.

1283
01:23:11,812 --> 01:23:15,773
And it was your job
to enforce these laws.

1284
01:23:15,903 --> 01:23:17,122
Of course,
that's impossible.

1285
01:23:18,254 --> 01:23:19,429
The way I see it,

1286
01:23:19,559 --> 01:23:21,474
society gets the kind of
criminals it deserves.

1287
01:23:22,780 --> 01:23:24,825
The more it clamps down,

1288
01:23:24,956 --> 01:23:28,177
the more those of us
that are truly free

1289
01:23:28,307 --> 01:23:29,700
must rise up against it.

1290
01:23:33,660 --> 01:23:34,574
[humming]

1291
01:23:38,491 --> 01:23:40,015
[car horn honks]

1292
01:23:50,808 --> 01:23:52,201
[honking]

1293
01:24:00,035 --> 01:24:01,558
Your wheel!
Your wheel!

1294
01:24:02,863 --> 01:24:04,648
-Your wheel!
-[honking]

1295
01:24:05,518 --> 01:24:07,477
Yeah! Yeah!

1296
01:24:07,607 --> 01:24:08,826
Pull over!

1297
01:24:08,956 --> 01:24:10,349
Pull over!

1298
01:24:24,059 --> 01:24:26,365
[car door opens and closes]

1299
01:24:31,979 --> 01:24:34,417
Sorry. I didn't mean
to frighten you,

1300
01:24:34,547 --> 01:24:37,507
but I noticed that
your left rear wheel
seemed to be wobbling.

1301
01:24:37,637 --> 01:24:38,725
It's not too bad,
but I think

1302
01:24:38,856 --> 01:24:41,337
you should
get it checked as soon
as possible.

1303
01:24:41,467 --> 01:24:43,600
[Lucca making muffled yells]

1304
01:24:43,730 --> 01:24:45,689
Yeah, I'd get that
looked at.

1305
01:24:45,819 --> 01:24:46,951
I will, thanks.

1306
01:24:47,082 --> 01:24:48,344
There's
a service station

1307
01:24:48,474 --> 01:24:50,955
about 10 miles
up the road.

1308
01:24:51,086 --> 01:24:53,871
It's open 24 hours
and it's just off
the freeway.

1309
01:24:57,527 --> 01:24:58,571
Look...

1310
01:24:59,659 --> 01:25:00,660
Uh...

1311
01:25:01,444 --> 01:25:02,488
Look...

1312
01:25:04,490 --> 01:25:06,362
If it'll make you
feel any better,

1313
01:25:06,492 --> 01:25:07,885
I've got a lug wrench
in my trunk.

1314
01:25:08,015 --> 01:25:09,756
I could tighten it up
for you a little.

1315
01:25:09,887 --> 01:25:12,107
You know, just to get you
to the station.

1316
01:25:16,720 --> 01:25:17,895
Well, if it wouldn't be
too much trouble.

1317
01:25:18,025 --> 01:25:20,332
Not at all.

1318
01:25:20,463 --> 01:25:21,638
[humming theme to <i>Big Valley]</i>

1319
01:25:29,863 --> 01:25:31,430
[groaning]

1320
01:25:37,915 --> 01:25:39,525
Here we go!

1321
01:25:39,656 --> 01:25:40,787
Oh, you don't
have to get out.

1322
01:25:40,918 --> 01:25:42,441
Uh, I can
take care of it.

1323
01:25:44,443 --> 01:25:45,488
[straining]

1324
01:25:45,618 --> 01:25:46,967
[resumes humming]

1325
01:25:47,098 --> 01:25:48,708
You live around here?

1326
01:25:48,839 --> 01:25:50,449
Over in San Ramon.
How about you?

1327
01:25:50,754 --> 01:25:51,929
Napa.

1328
01:25:52,059 --> 01:25:53,713
Napa?

1329
01:25:53,844 --> 01:25:56,629
Hey. It's nice
out that way.

1330
01:25:56,760 --> 01:25:58,631
I'm headed
up to my Mom's place
in Chico.

1331
01:25:59,676 --> 01:26:00,938
I like driving at night.

1332
01:26:02,374 --> 01:26:03,636
Less traffic.

1333
01:26:05,421 --> 01:26:06,465
There.

1334
01:26:07,423 --> 01:26:08,859
That ought to do it.

1335
01:26:08,989 --> 01:26:10,643
Well, thank you.
I appreciate it.

1336
01:26:10,774 --> 01:26:12,384
Oh, not at all.

1337
01:26:12,515 --> 01:26:14,169
You get that
looked at, huh?

1338
01:26:15,605 --> 01:26:16,693
[humming]

1339
01:26:17,563 --> 01:26:18,738
[starts engine]

1340
01:26:22,568 --> 01:26:23,961
[Lloyd starts car]

1341
01:27:12,836 --> 01:27:14,054
[Lloyd] Are you okay?

1342
01:27:14,185 --> 01:27:15,926
[woman] I think so.

1343
01:27:16,056 --> 01:27:17,493
You sure
you're not hurt?

1344
01:27:17,623 --> 01:27:18,624
I'm just...

1345
01:27:18,755 --> 01:27:20,191
I'm just
a little shook up.

1346
01:27:20,322 --> 01:27:22,498
Must've been worse
than it looked.

1347
01:27:22,628 --> 01:27:23,629
I thought
you could make it

1348
01:27:23,760 --> 01:27:26,284
to the gas station
for sure.

1349
01:27:26,415 --> 01:27:28,547
I'm just glad that
you're nice enough
to help out.

1350
01:27:40,820 --> 01:27:42,387
Do you mind?

1351
01:27:42,518 --> 01:27:43,867
Oh, heck no.

1352
01:27:43,997 --> 01:27:45,608
I used to smoke
for 25 years,

1353
01:27:45,738 --> 01:27:47,436
but I had to stop.

1354
01:27:47,566 --> 01:27:48,872
[inhales deeply]

1355
01:27:49,002 --> 01:27:51,440
Ahh. I still love
the smell of them.

1356
01:27:53,703 --> 01:27:56,271
Nothing's ever happened
to me like that before.

1357
01:27:57,794 --> 01:28:00,013
All of a sudden,
the wheel started
shaking.

1358
01:28:00,144 --> 01:28:02,799
There was nothing
I could do but
hold on for the ride.

1359
01:28:02,929 --> 01:28:04,627
That's all you can do.

1360
01:28:11,590 --> 01:28:12,548
What do you do in, uh,

1361
01:28:13,723 --> 01:28:14,767
Napa?

1362
01:28:18,205 --> 01:28:20,947
I work in a bank.
The Wells Fargo.

1363
01:28:21,078 --> 01:28:22,732
How about you?

1364
01:28:22,862 --> 01:28:25,561
I'm in the extermination
business.

1365
01:28:25,691 --> 01:28:27,780
Have been for about
20 years, I guess.

1366
01:28:35,745 --> 01:28:37,529
[groaning]

1367
01:28:37,660 --> 01:28:39,749
Do you always go around
helping people
on the road like this?

1368
01:28:40,880 --> 01:28:41,794
Yes.

1369
01:28:43,883 --> 01:28:45,885
I try to help
as often as I can.

1370
01:28:46,843 --> 01:28:48,845
[pounding]

1371
01:28:51,021 --> 01:28:52,936
[laughing]

1372
01:28:53,066 --> 01:28:53,980
[muffled yell]

1373
01:28:54,111 --> 01:28:56,896
See how easy it is, Jon?

1374
01:28:57,027 --> 01:29:00,030
Do you see how
they're just out there
waiting to be taken?

1375
01:29:02,162 --> 01:29:04,426
Oh, she knows
she's going to die.

1376
01:29:04,556 --> 01:29:05,688
[muffled yelling]

1377
01:29:05,818 --> 01:29:07,646
And it's exhilarating.

1378
01:29:08,865 --> 01:29:10,040
That moment
of recognition.

1379
01:29:12,172 --> 01:29:14,479
That moment
when she realizes

1380
01:29:16,307 --> 01:29:17,613
that she is mine.

1381
01:29:19,179 --> 01:29:21,007
That her last breath

1382
01:29:22,226 --> 01:29:23,662
will be mine.

1383
01:29:25,664 --> 01:29:26,796
[Lloyd] Shit!

1384
01:29:26,926 --> 01:29:28,058
[woman] No!

1385
01:29:31,975 --> 01:29:33,193
[muffled yelling]

1386
01:29:33,324 --> 01:29:34,934
Make all the noise
you want!

1387
01:29:36,153 --> 01:29:37,676
[muffled yelling]

1388
01:29:46,381 --> 01:29:48,557
[Lloyd breathing heavily]

1389
01:29:48,687 --> 01:29:50,602
[Lloyd chuckles]

1390
01:29:50,733 --> 01:29:52,125
[gun firing repeatedly]

1391
01:29:58,697 --> 01:29:59,916
[firing continues]

1392
01:30:01,787 --> 01:30:03,398
[muffled yell]

1393
01:30:07,924 --> 01:30:09,404
Happy birthday.

1394
01:30:19,065 --> 01:30:20,763
[turn signal clicking]

1395
01:30:28,945 --> 01:30:30,555
[metallic scraping]

1396
01:30:35,342 --> 01:30:37,040
[muffled coughing]

1397
01:30:57,364 --> 01:30:59,628
These gloves just
don't seem to fit.

1398
01:31:05,416 --> 01:31:06,983
[muffled coughing]

1399
01:31:10,769 --> 01:31:12,902
What's wrong, Jon?

1400
01:31:13,032 --> 01:31:15,426
Don't you recognize
your old precinct?

1401
01:31:15,557 --> 01:31:18,473
Isn't this where
you wanted our tour
to end? Huh?

1402
01:31:30,006 --> 01:31:31,094
[metal detector buzzer sounds]

1403
01:31:31,224 --> 01:31:32,791
Excuse me, you...
Hey, whoa.

1404
01:31:33,357 --> 01:31:34,619
Jesus!

1405
01:31:35,054 --> 01:31:36,142
Get down!

1406
01:31:36,273 --> 01:31:37,622
Get down!

1407
01:31:37,753 --> 01:31:39,058
[people screaming]

1408
01:31:48,503 --> 01:31:50,113
[police officer]
Come on, bro.

1409
01:31:50,243 --> 01:31:51,767
Come on,
put the gun down.

1410
01:31:51,897 --> 01:31:53,116
Now!

1411
01:31:53,246 --> 01:31:55,292
Come on. You don't
want to die, right?

1412
01:31:55,422 --> 01:31:57,642
[coughing]

1413
01:31:57,773 --> 01:31:59,122
Don't make me do it.

1414
01:31:59,252 --> 01:32:02,342
-Are you going
to shoot me?
-Get down!

1415
01:32:02,473 --> 01:32:04,780
Or should I confess?
Is that what
you want me to do?

1416
01:32:04,910 --> 01:32:06,085
Huh?

1417
01:32:06,216 --> 01:32:07,783
-It's your move.
-Put it down!

1418
01:32:07,913 --> 01:32:08,958
It's your gun.

1419
01:32:09,088 --> 01:32:10,568
Your gloves.

1420
01:32:10,699 --> 01:32:12,048
Your car.

1421
01:32:12,178 --> 01:32:13,832
Your corpus delicti.

1422
01:32:16,966 --> 01:32:18,228
You're going down, Jon.

1423
01:32:20,186 --> 01:32:22,014
But at least as you lay
dying in your cell,

1424
01:32:22,145 --> 01:32:24,190
you'll know
that you were right.

1425
01:32:24,321 --> 01:32:26,758
At least
you'll have that.

1426
01:32:29,152 --> 01:32:33,156
It was me
all these years.

1427
01:32:33,286 --> 01:32:36,376
And it'll keep being me
long after you're gone.

1428
01:32:36,507 --> 01:32:38,683
Put the gun down,
or I'll drop you!

1429
01:32:39,510 --> 01:32:40,859
I'll miss you, Jon.

1430
01:32:44,907 --> 01:32:46,256
Put the gun down
on the ground now!

1431
01:32:46,386 --> 01:32:49,041
But I promise
to think of you
each and every time.

1432
01:32:51,043 --> 01:32:53,176
There.
Feel better?

1433
01:32:53,306 --> 01:32:54,743
Last chance!
I will drop you!

1434
01:32:56,832 --> 01:32:58,137
Now!

1435
01:32:58,268 --> 01:32:59,704
[woman screams]

1436
01:33:13,979 --> 01:33:15,198
[siren wailing]

1437
01:33:16,329 --> 01:33:17,896
I feel like shit.

1438
01:33:19,506 --> 01:33:20,812
[groans]

1439
01:33:25,512 --> 01:33:26,775
[coughs]

